					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12652581#post-4391810</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12652581/scp-4358#post-4391810</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 07 Oct 2019 23:21:57 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Willa Winslow</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1367581</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is wonderful! It really captures the varied feelings that can well up within you in these places. Giving the entry a placement in time helps with this too - finding a lovers lane, you can't help but wonder about both its past and its future, what the people who find shelter there in the years to come will look like.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12652581#post-4391747</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12652581/scp-4358#post-4391747</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 07 Oct 2019 22:00:34 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>aismallard</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4598089</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Pleasant little work. I like the implication that their antiestablishment behavior is a reaction to the containment and socially repressive mores.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Nitpick</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Nitpick</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>that were considered taboo at the time, i.e. of a homosexual nature.</p> </blockquote> <p>Should be &quot;e.g.&quot;, since it's not the only kind of taboo relationship.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12652581#post-4391652</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12652581/scp-4358#post-4391652</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 07 Oct 2019 19:22:38 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>kinchtheknifeblade</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1345012</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>No the final line says the containment procedures are to be rewritten immediately. They just haven't gotten to it yet. I present my SCPs as living documents, and this is a snapshot taken directly after this was discovered but before the drafting of new containment procedures. In order to, like, keep the final stinger a surprise.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12652581#post-4391650</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12652581/scp-4358#post-4391650</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 07 Oct 2019 19:20:40 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Purplayoss</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5227700</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is a very nice and interesting SCP. Anomalous love stories are always nice, and I was just reading <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2203">SCP-2203</a> earlier.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Minor&nbsp;Nitpick</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-Minor&nbsp;Nitpick</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>The final incident mentions various non-human species becoming instances of SCP-4358-ADAM and -EVE, then says that the CONPROCS have been modified accordingly. However, no mention is made to local fauna in the containment procedures.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>Besides that, +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
